page.title: 09Winnall Moors.
page.content: Winnall Moors will be open to the public on 11th August which is great because it is all wild life. You can see a lot of wild flowers and wild birds which make a lovely noise altogether.The River Itchen flows through Winnall Moors. Winnall Moors covers an area of 100 acres and 40 acres will be open to the public.The northern part of Winnall Moors is owned by Hampshire and Isle Of Wight Naturalist Trust and the southern part is owned by Winchester City Council. They have dug a pond for the creatures and insects which live in still water because the River Itchen is fast flowing .The Moors were once water meadows.The animals they have are foxes, otters, coots, moorhen, snipe, water voles and redshank.Among the plants are Willow, Alder, Hemlock, Ragged Robin and many more.
